%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 1cb8db85de55fa142bafb539466ab76c, type: 3}
  m_Name: TutorialDatabase
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  entries:
  - triggerKey: game_start
    message: Welcome to Incinder!\nYou are a Seeker, sent alone into the depths of
      the Cathedral to retrieve an ancient blood goblet. Traverse its crumbling rooms,
      loot chests for helpful items, and face the creatures that lurk within. Use
      the shadows to your advantage, harness blood magic to overcome those who stand
      in your way and find the goblet, and your mission is complete.\nLeft-click
      anywhere to move.
  - triggerKey: first_move
    message: You're on the move!\nOutside of combat you can move freely. Want to
      investigate the room without moving? Use WASD to move the camera, and hold
      right-click to pivot it.
  - triggerKey: first_ability_selected
    message: Abilities are your main tools in combat. Press 1, 2, or 3, or click
      the buttons at the bottom to select one, then click a target/area to cast it.
      Hover over the ability buttons to learn each ability's details. To cancel targeting,
      press the same ability key again or switch to a different one.
  - triggerKey: first_attack
    message: Good job, you got them!\nBefore confirming a target during combat, you
      can press Space to gamble a coin flip. Success boosts the ability's damage
      by 50%, but failure halves it. You can see enemy health by hovering over them,
      or at the top of the screen in combat.
  - triggerKey: first_spotted
    message: You've been spotted!\nThe enemy is on their way to destroy you. Next
      time try staying in the shadows to slip past undetected, or strike first before
      they see you to get the drop on them.
  - triggerKey: first_combat
    message: Combat has begun!\nThe coins at the bottom right are your Action Points
      - spend them to use your abilities. However, if you don't use all your coins
      in one turn you can carry one over to your next turn. The ring around the seeker
      shows your maximum movement distance for this turn.
  - triggerKey: first_damage_taken
    message: You took a hit!\nKeep an eye on your health in the bottom left. If it
      reaches zero, your quest is over, that's a complete reset back to the very
      beginning.
  - triggerKey: first_combat_win
    message: Victory!\nKeep exploring, somewhere in these ruins lies a powerful artifact,
      and it won't find itself. If things get too dangerous, try stealthing through
      the shadows to slip past enemies undetected. Good luck on your quest!
  - triggerKey: first_chest_open
    message: You found some items!\nSelect one of 3 options to take with you. After,
      press Tab or click the bag icon in the bottom right to open your inventory,
      where you can click items to equip or unequip them. You can only have 5 items
      equipped at a time.
